            "letterSpacing": 0,
            "lineHeight": 1.65,
            "text": "Typography is the art and technique of arranging type to make written language legible, readable, and appealing when displayed. The arrangement of type involves selecting typefaces, point sizes, line lengths, line-spacing (leading), and letter-spacing (tracking), as well as adjusting the space between pairs of letters (kerning). This paragraph intentionally wraps across multiple lines to stress-test how the HTML-to-PPTX pipeline handles line breaks, word wrapping, and paragraph reflow at various container widths. It should maintain consistent leading and produce clean, readable output regardless of the rendering engine.",
            "textTransform": "none",
          },
        ],
        "text": "Typography is the art and technique of arranging type to make written language legible, readable, and appealing when displayed. The arrangement of type involves selecting typefaces, point sizes, line lengths, line-spacing (leading), and letter-spacing (tracking), as well as adjusting the space between pairs of letters (kerning). This paragraph intentionally wraps across multiple lines to stress-test how the HTML-to-PPTX pipeline handles line breaks, word wrapping, and paragraph reflow at various container widths. It should maintain consistent leading and produce clean, readable output regardless of the rendering engine.",
